go_data.justification: Dm1 is the active resting state of Drosophila complex I, which is part of the electron transport chain.
Dm1 is a state of Drosophila complex I, which is located in the mitochondrion.
Dm1 is the active resting state of Drosophila complex I, which has NADH dehydrogenase activity.
The Dm1 state has a sealed and closed ubiquinone-binding site, indicating that it is capable of binding ubiquinone.
